---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Contact - Leszek Pomianowski">
  <div class="page">
    <h1>Contact</h1>
    <p>
      Want to chat about a project or collaborate on something cool? I'm usually up for discussing 
      .NET stuff, distributed systems, or developer tools.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Email</h2>
    <p>
      Drop me a line at: <strong>support at lepo.co</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      Just replace "at" with @ when you email. I usually get back to people within a day or two.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Professional Work</h2>
    <p>
      If you need consulting or technical help, check out <a href="/support/">the support page</a> 
      to see what I can help with and whether I'm available.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Find Me Online</h2>
    <p>You can also find me here:</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>GitHub:</strong> 
        <a href="https://github.com/lepoco" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@lepoco</a> - 
        Where I keep my projects
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>GitHub Sponsors:</strong> 
        <a href="https://github.com/sponsors/pomianowski" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@pomianowski</a> - 
        If you want to support what I'm building
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Quick Note</h2>
    <p>
      When you reach out, it helps if you mention what you're working on and what kind of help 
      you're looking for. For open-source stuff, check the GitHub issues first - might already 
      be an answer there.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout> 
<style>
  .page {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  .page ul {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }
  
  .page li {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }
  
  .page h2 {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .page p {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
